    <item>
      <title>Options</title>
      <link>/pages/video-lectures-and-slides/options/data.json</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/pages/video-lectures-and-slides/options/data.json</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;video-lectures&#34;&gt;Video Lectures&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;h4 id=&#34;options-i&#34;&gt;Options I&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;../../../resources/part-ii-of-forward-and-futures-contracts-1/index.html&#34;&gt;Part I of Options&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt; This video lecture presents options, a derivative, as another kind of security. The two different kinds of options, calls and puts, and key terms used in describing options are defined.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;h4 id=&#34;options-ii&#34;&gt;Options II&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;../../../resources/part-ii-of-options/index.html&#34;&gt;Part II of Options&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt; This video lecture covers interpreting payoff diagrams of call and put options and how to use the diagrams in option strategizing and betting on volatility. A brief historical background for option-pricing theory is also given.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
